</i></p><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-14_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Public Health England (PHE) plays a crucial role in safeguarding the health and well-being of the population across the United Kingdom. Established in 2013, PHE is an executive agency of the Department of Health and Social Care. Its primary mission is to protect and improve the nation's health and to address health inequalities. In this blog, Dr Richard Dune will explore the role of PHE, highlighting its significance, providing key definitions, and offering best practice recommendations for implementing relevant legislation and regulations.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Previous" class="pf-slider-prev none hide"></button><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Next" class="pf-slider-next none hide"></button></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-8944" data-category="Collection Suggestion" data-name="Tea" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-kYHfwS doYKjf pf-16_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-hAcGzb cVhebe"><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-17_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-18_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-19_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key facts and statistics</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-21_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">PHE's impact on public health is substantial. Here are some key facts and statistics that illustrate its importance:







































</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-23_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-24_ pf-text-1"><strong>Funding and resources </strong>- PHE has a budget of over Â£4 billion annually, which it utilises to implement various public health initiatives.


</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-26_ pf-text-1"><strong>Health protection</strong> - PHE has played a pivotal role in responding to major health threats, including the COVID-19 pandemic, where it led testing and contact tracing efforts.




</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-28_ pf-text-1"><strong>Health improvement</strong> - PHE's campaigns, such as Change4Life and Stoptober, have successfully encouraged millions to adopt healthier lifestyles.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-30_ pf-text-1"><strong>Reducing health inequalities</strong> - PHE works to address health disparities by focusing on the most vulnerable populations, ensuring equitable access to health services.





</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-32_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-33_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-34_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-36_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">To understand the role of PHE, it is essential to define some key terms:







































</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-38_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-39_ pf-text-1"><strong>Public health</strong> - The science and practice of protecting and improving the health of a community through education, policy-making, and research for disease and injury prevention.


</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-41_ pf-text-1"><strong>Health inequality</strong> - Differences in health status or in the distribution of health determinants between different population groups.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-43_ pf-text-1"><strong>Health protection </strong>- Activities designed to protect individuals and populations from infectious diseases and environmental hazards.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-45_ pf-text-1"><strong>Health improvement</strong> - Efforts aimed at improving the health of individuals and communities by promoting healthy lifestyles and reducing risk factors.



</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-47_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-48_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-49_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommended best practices for implementing relevant legislation and regulations</h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-51_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Health protection legislation</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-53_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">PHE enforces several pieces of legislation to protect public health. Key regulations include:








































</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-55_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-56_ pf-text-1"><strong>Health Protection (Notification) Regulations 2010 </strong>- Mandates the notification of infectious diseases by healthcare providers, enabling PHE to monitor and respond to outbreaks.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-58_ pf-text-1"><strong>Control of Substances Hazardous to Health (COSHH) Regulations 2002</strong> - Requires employers to control substances that can harm health, with PHE guiding safe practices.



</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-60_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Health improvement initiatives</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-62_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">PHE's health improvement initiatives are governed by various policies and frameworks:








































</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-64_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-65_ pf-text-1"><strong>Public health outcomes framework </strong>- Sets out desired outcomes for public health and the indicators that will be used to measure improvements.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-67_ pf-text-1"><strong>Local Authority Public Health Grant</strong> - Provides funding to local authorities to deliver public health services, with PHE offering support and guidance.



</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-69_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Reducing health inequalities</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-71_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">PHE collaborates with multiple stakeholders to reduce health inequalities:









































</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-73_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-74_ pf-text-1"><strong>Health equity in England </strong>- The Marmot Review 10 Years On: A comprehensive review that highlights the need for action to address social determinants of health and reduce health disparities.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-76_ pf-text-1"><strong>Every mind matters </strong>- A mental health campaign aimed at improving mental well-being across different demographic groups.




</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-78_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-79_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-80_ pf-heading-1-h3">The role of PHE in health protection
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-82_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">PHE's health protection function involves monitoring and responding to infectious diseases, environmental hazards, and other threats to public health. The agency operates a national surveillance system to detect outbreaks and implements measures to control their spread. For instance, during the COVID-19 pandemic, PHE's efforts in testing, contact tracing, and public communication were crucial in managing the crisis.






































</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-84_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-85_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-86_ pf-heading-1-h3">Promoting health improvement
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-88_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Health improvement is a core aspect of PHE's work. The agency runs national campaigns to promote healthier lifestyles, focusing on issues such as smoking cessation, obesity reduction, and physical activity. Programmes like Change4Life have been instrumental in encouraging healthier eating and increased physical activity among children and families.






































</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-90_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-91_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-92_ pf-heading-1-h3">Addressing health inequalities
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-94_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">PHE is dedicated to reducing health inequalities by ensuring that public health services are accessible to all, particularly vulnerable and disadvantaged groups. This involves working with local authorities, healthcare providers, and community organisations to deliver targeted interventions. By addressing the social determinants of health, PHE aims to create a fairer, healthier society.








































</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-96_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-97_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-98_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommendations
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-100_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">To effectively implement PHE's guidelines and regulations, organisations should:







































</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-102_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-103_ pf-text-1"><strong>Stay informed</strong> - Keep up to date with the latest public health information and guidelines from PHE.


</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-105_ pf-text-1"><strong>Implement training programmes </strong>- Provide comprehensive training for staff on health protection and improvement practices.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-107_ pf-text-1"><strong>Utilise compliance tools </strong>- Adopt tools like ComplyPlusâ¢ to manage legislative and regulatory compliance effectively.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-109_ pf-text-1"><strong>Promote healthy lifestyles</strong> - Encourage and facilitate healthy behaviours within the workplace and the community.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-111_ pf-text-1"><strong>Engage with local health initiatives </strong>- Collaborate with local health authorities and participate in community health programmes.




